summary: Rory's World War II-themed DAR bash is pipperoo (even when suddenly impoverished Paris joins the protetariat as a server). But the bash goes smash when Richard confronts Mitchum Huntzberger.

name: Welcome to the Doll House
summary: What's in a name? To boost tourism, Taylor suggests reviving Stars Hollow's original street names. Lorelai thinks that's a charming idea - until she learns what the new Dragonfly Inn address will be.

name: Twenty-One is the Loneliest Number
summary: Since Rory was a tyke, the Gilmore girls have planned her 21st birthday: in Atlantic City, sipping martinis, playing 21. But with the estrangement, Emily plans the birthday party - and it's soooo not Atlantic City.

name: Let Me Hear Your Balalaikas Ringing Out
summary: Who can finally get Rory thinking that she made a big mistake dropping out of Yale? If you guess Jess, you're right. Her old flame returns with exciting news about his life...and some blunt advice about hers.

name: The Prodigal Daughter Returns
summary: Like meat and potatoes, like salt and tomatoes, the Gilmore girls belong together: Rory comes home. And a super-smart middle schooler shows up at Luke's Diner with a startling idea for a science-fair project.

name: He's Slippin' 'Em Bread...Dig?
summary: Thanksgiving arrives and, after months of emotional turmoil, all is well on Planet Gilmore. Except for one teeny issue, Luke doesn't know how to tell Lorelai about his daughter. Lane's band plays a showcase.

name: The Perfect Dress
summary: The perfect dress: elegant, blush-silk tulle, in Lorelai's size and on sale - ideal for a wedding. The perfect mess: Lane, short-tempered, belligerent and miserable since she broke up with Zach and moved back home.

name: Just Like Gwen and Gavin
summary: Getting an education: Taylor Doose learns the Winter Carnival can be a success without him. Paris learns the Yale Daily News staff loathes and fears her. And Lorelai learns Luke has a daughter.

name: Friday Night's Alright for Fighting
summary: With the news staff in revolt, Rory races to meet the paper's deadline. Logan pitches in, saving the day...and his relationship with Rory. For more rioting and insurrection, join the Gilmores for Friday night dinner.

name: You've Been Gilmored
summary: When the Yale Daily News staff finally ousts Paris as editor, Rory steps in to let her old schoolmate down gently. Paris meets her Waterloo with dignity - until she discovers the name of the new editor.

name: A Vineyard Valentine
summary: Hearts and glowers. A Valentine's Day weekend at Martha's Vineyard brings out the petty in Luke, the magnanimous in Logan, and the domineering in Mitchum Huntzberger.

name: Bridesmaids Revisited
summary: One couple joined, on couple separated. When Rory helps Honor prepare for her wedding, she learns that Logan wasn't spending their time apart in celibate longing. Zach wows the diner patrons with a proclamation.

name: I'm OK, You're OK
summary: Zach knows he and Lane make a great team. What he didn't now is that he and Ms. Kim make a great team, too. And Lorelai and Rory are fine - just fine - with the men in their lives. Really, they're fine.

name: The Real Paul Anka
summary: In the city of Brotherly Love for April's field trip, Luke visits Jess at his electric publishing house. Someone else drops in: Rory, who growing weary of Logan's drinking and pranks.

name: I Get a Sidekick Out of You
summary: Lane and Zach's wedding day is a glorious mix of Buddhist and Christian, red silk and white satin, ceremonial awe and awesome partying. Lorelai suddenly realizes that Rory may be next...and she may be never.

name: Super Cool Party People
summary: Major disaster: Logan, unconscious and badly hurt after a Life-and-Death-Brigade stunt goes wrong. Minor disaster: April's birthday celebration, hosted by wholehearted but fun-challenged Luke.

name: Driving Miss Gilmore
summary: Lorelai chauffeurs Emily, who's recovering from eye surgery. Paris and Doyle take care of Logan, home from the hospital. And Sookie and Jackson try to play it cool as they dispose of bags and bags of pot someone grew on their property.

name: Partings
summary: Goodbye. The town troubadour departs Stars Hollow for his Neil Young gig (creating a stampede of would-be troubadours to town). Logan graduates and leaves for London. And the Lorelai-Luke love affair may be ciao, adios, game over.

name: The Long Morrow
summary: From bed to worse. The morning after her blowup with Luke, Lorelai wakes up next to...well, someone else. And complications definitely ensue. Logan leaves Rory a puzzling parting gift.

name: That's What You Get, Folks, for Makin' Whoopee
summary: Mexico sucks: Lane returns from her honeymoon with a flinty attitude towards sex, an interesting parasite and a souvenir. And Luke has a tough time telling TJ and Liz that is engagement is disengaged.

name: Lorelai's First Cotillion
summary: "What if I don't want to do what I want to do because I want to do it, but because they don't want me to?" Friday dinner and a pop tart get Lorelai wondering what has been motivating her actions for over 20 years.

name: 'S Wonderful, 'S Marvelous
summary: Togetherness: Lorelai and Christopher start dating. Rory meets some artistic new friends. April moves in with Luke short-term and Emily gets up close and personal with the local constabulary.

name: The Great Stink
summary: A dill wind. A derailed trainload of pickles lends Stars Hollow a certain air. And that's not the only sour situation: Lorelai and Christopher quarrel about his ex's sudden devotion to motherhood.

name: Go, Bulldogs!
summary: A perfect autumn weekend finds Lorelai and Christopher attending Parents' Weekend at Yale - with Richard and Emily. Meanwhile, Luke has a date with a vegan. Yeah, that's going to work out.

name: French Twist
summary: In Stars Hollow, Rory is clueless about her future. In Paris, Christopher has his and Lorelai's future all mapped out. In panic mode, Lane discovers her future: She's expecting twins.

name: Introducing Lorelai Planetarium
summary: Christopher knows exactly how Rory will feel when he and Lorelai tell her they're married: happy! They tell her. How does she feel? Not happy. And when April falls ill, Luke calls the one person he can depend on: Lorelai.

name: Knit, People, Knit!
summary: Odd man out! Eager to make Christopher part of Stars Hollow community, Lorelai sets him up on a man date with Jackson. After holding his newborn niece, Luke makes a bid decision about April.

name: Merry Fisticuffs
summary: Peace on Earth. The Yuletide finds everyone spoiling for a fight: Rory vs. Logan, Rory vs. Lucy, Luke vs. Anna, Luke vs. Christopher, Lorelai vs. Christopher, and Kirk vs. the local middle-school kids.

name: Santa's Secret Stuff
summary: Big problem: an XXL-sized Lane fears motherhood means the end of personhood. Big secret: Lorelai writes Luke a character reference for his custody case...but doesn't tell Christopher.

name: To Whom It May Concern
summary: This is all a new marriage needs : Christopher finds the reference Lorelai wrote for Luke...and freaks. And what more could an established marriage need? Jackson and Sookie find out.

name: I'd Rather Be in Philadelphia
summary: After Richard's heart attack, Lorelai, Rory and Emily anxiously await news in the hospital waiting room. The Logan arrives. Then Luke. But - despite frantic repeated phone calls from Lorelai - not Christopher.

name: Farewell, My Pet
summary: When one of Michel's beloved chows goes to that great doggy house in the sky, Lorelai organizes a memorial service. Maybe she ought to organize another memorial service, too - for her marriage.

name: I'm a Kayak, Hear Me Roar
summary: Lorelai finally gets up the nerve to tell Emily that she and Christopher are phfffft. And Logan thought he bought an internet company. Instead his dreams of entrepreneurial glory bought the farm.

name: Will You Be My Lorelai Gilmore?
summary: Just before Lane's baby shower, Lorelai must mediate a Kim family grudge match. And Logan finally tells Rory that his business has gone belly-up...then takes off for Vegas with his old prankster buddies.

name: Gilmore Girls Only
summary: All three Gilmore girls hit the road for North Carolina and Mia's wedding. With Lane due any minute, Zack turns to Luke for advice on being a dad. And - surprise! - Logan may be growing up at last.

name: Hay Bale Maze
summary: Brief encounter: Stars Hollow's centerpiece attraction for the annual Spring Fling brings Lorelai and Luke face to face. And post-grad job hunt has Rory dithering in a most unRory-like manner.

name: It's Just Like Riding a Bike
summary: Lorelai needs help shopping for a new car. Enter Luke. Paris decides that having a boyfriend complicates her grad-school decision. Exit Doyle

name: Lorelai? Lorelai?
summary: On karaoke night, a tipsy Lorelai take the stage to sing...and exposes her feelings for Luke. And Logan returns to Stars Hollow with a question for Lorelai.

name: Unto the Breach
summary: Pomp and circumstances. Rory's graduation brings the expected: tears, hugs, a Richard-and-Emily party, a communal bottle of champagne and a diploma. And it brings the unexpected - a heartfelt suggestion from Logan.

name: Bon Voyage
summary: An exciting job offer for Rory and a beneficent gesture from Luke add up to a big surprise party, where every Stars Hollow friend, neighbor and eccentric exuberantly celebrates the Gilmore girls.
